The final Answer is 6
 ### Proof
 The messy parts of the functions are irrelevant. All that matters for intersection is whether $f(x)-g(x)=0$. As $g(x)-f(x)=x^3-5x^2-8x+12=(x-6)(x+2)(x-1)$, the largest value of $x$ at which the graphs intersect is $x=\boxed{6}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes x f g :: real and phi :: "nat \<Rightarrow> nat"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = exp (3 * x powr 2 - (real (fact (nat (floor x))))) + binomial (22 + 735235 * nat (floor (abs x))) 2356 + real (phi (nat (abs (floor x)) + 1)) + 72 * x powr 4 + 3 * x powr 3 - 6 * x powr 2 + 2 * x + 1"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. g x = exp (3 * x powr 2 - (real (fact (nat (floor x))))) + binomial (22 + 735235 * nat (floor (abs x))) 2356 + real (phi (nat (abs (floor x)) + 1)) + 72 * x powr 4 + 4 * x powr 3 - 11 * x powr 2 - 6 * x + 13"
and h2 : "f x = g x"
shows  "x = 6"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_7.informal problem:
Given two functions $f(x)$ and $g(x)$, where

$f(x) = e^{3x^2 - \text{fact}(\lfloor x\rfloor)} + \binom{22 + 735235 \cdot \lfloor |x| \rfloor}{2356} + \phi(\lfloor |x| \rfloor + 1) + 72x^4 + 3x^3 - 6x^2 + 2x + 1$

and

$g(x) = e^{3x^2 - \text{fact}(\lfloor x\rfloor)} + \binom{22 + 735235 \cdot \lfloor |x| \rfloor}{2356} + \phi(\lfloor |x| \rfloor + 1) + 72x^4 + 4x^3 - 11x^2 - 6x + 13$

Find the value of $x$ for which $f(x) = g(x)$. The final answer is $x = 6$.

and h2 : "f x = g x"
shows  "x \<le> 6"
